A woman has been arrested for attempting to sell her newborn in Mlolongo, Machakos county. The woman was arrested by the Mlolongo division security team led by assistant county commissioner Dennis Onganga on Wednesday. Onganga said the woman attempted to sell the child at Sh60,000, citing financial challenges. According to his birth certificate, the baby was born on September 2, 2020 at Machakos Level 5 Hospital. Onganga said the child was rescued and together with the mother was taken to Mlolongo police station. The matter was booked under OB NO: 82/21/10/2020. "The baby has been taken to Mahali pa Maisha Rescue Home,‚Äù Onganga said.